    <!-- ==========================================
         RESEARCH
         ========================================== -->
    <section class="section" id="research" aria-labelledby="research-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="content-width">
          <div class="section-header">
            <span class="section-label">Research</span>
            <h2 id="research-heading">Understanding cognitive decline</h2>
          </div>

          <p class="lead">
            We conduct and support research into how cognitive decline progresses, what interventions make a meaningful difference, and how personal identity can be documented and preserved.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our research is informed by real-world interviews with families and caregivers &mdash; not just clinical data. We collaborate with researchers, clinicians, and community organizations to develop frameworks that are practical, ethical, and grounded in lived experience.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- ==========================================
         TECHNOLOGY
         ========================================== -->
    <section class="section section--cream" id="technology" aria-labelledby="technology-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="content-width">
          <div class="section-header">
            <span class="section-label">Technology</span>
            <h2 id="technology-heading">Practical tools for families</h2>
          </div>

          <p class="lead">
            We explore and develop technology that helps families manage the daily realities of cognitive decline. This includes tools for memory documentation, caregiver coordination, and communication support.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our approach to technology is simple: it should serve people, not complicate their lives. We test everything with real families before we build it, and we never deploy technology without understanding its human impact.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- ==========================================
         EDUCATION & FAMILY SUPPORT
         ========================================== -->
    <section class="section" id="family-support" aria-labelledby="family-support-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="content-width">
          <div class="section-header">
            <span class="section-label">Family Support</span>
            <h2 id="family-support-heading">Resources for caregivers and families</h2>
          </div>

          <p class="lead">
            Caregiving is demanding work. We provide guides, community resources, and direct support to families navigating cognitive decline.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our materials are built from interviews with caregivers who told us what they actually needed &mdash; practical guidance, emotional support, and the assurance that they are not alone. We also offer connection programs that bring families together with others who understand the journey.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


